summary: When Taylor posted that image of the Palm Trees on Oscar Sunday, I saw it as a tribute to old Hollywood, and she was just...
body:
When Taylor posted that image of the Palm Trees on Oscar Sunday, I saw it as a tribute to old Hollywood, and she was just letting us know she was in California, preparing for the Oscars.  The photo was classic looking.  The Oscars are  grandiose event.  I remember feeling this on that day.  

It got so blown up to be about the Album, and who knows what is to come.  But I think it was just a little Hollywood creative palm trees/Oscars nod.  Just wanted to get this off my chest

summary:
COLLECTIBLES ON YOUR BOOKSHELF
 I'm really getting back into posting Top 5 Wednesdays and this week it's not entirely about...
caption:
COLLECTIBLES ON YOUR BOOKSHELF

I’m really getting back into posting Top 5 Wednesdays and this week it’s not entirely about books which is cool. Today it’s 5 collectible items on your bookshelf.

This can be mugs, bookmarks, Funko pops or whatever else you have on there that may be significant. I did cheat a little, but I still think it’s valid enough to be on my top 5 list since it’s technically on my bookshelf. Anyway, let’s get into it.

5. Ceramic Hogwarts Express

I have this small but heavy ornament of the Hogwarts Express. I absolutely love it and it adds that bit of magic to my bookshelf, as if it’s on its way to Hogwarts with Harry, Ron and Hermione. My cousin gifted it to me last year along with a small Slytherin crest, but I just love the Hogwarts train so much. Soon as I received it, I just knew it was going on my shelf.

4. Taylor Swift Reputation Magazines Volumes 1 & 2

These magazines were supposed to be limited edition but they’re still floating around online. These gorgeous magazines sit facing out on the bottom of my bookshelf and if you don’t know me, I am the biggest Swiftie! I’ve loved Taylor and her music for 10 years now. They’re absolutely stunning and I also have a Taylor Swift Photo Frame with a picture of my nephew which is without a doubt the most special thing on my shelf, but for the sake of this post, it won’t be on this top 5 list just because.

3. Beauty and the Beast Music Box

I adore everything Beauty and the Beast and last Christmas my best friend gave me a small music box that plays ‘A Tale as Old as Time’ that I absolutely love! It sits proudly on the top shelf flanked by mini Beast and Belle figurines. It’s beautiful, and every now and again I’ll take it down and play it.

2. Hunted ARC by Meagan Spooner

This is one of my most cherished books - as a story, and the physical copy. I read Hunted before it released and was searching for a physical ARC copy of it because I loved it so much. Meagan saw how much I adored her book and raved about it that she reached out and said she’d send me an ARC.

Not only was it one of my defining moments as a book blogger to have an author reach out to me, but also because she so kindly offered and signed and personalised it, too. To this day, I’m so grateful and am in love with the story she told. I still can’t believe that happened!

1. My Leigh Bardugo/Grisha shelf

Look, it’s still on my bookshelf and it counts, okay! No.1 goes to my entire Bardugo shelf that houses special editions, signed copies, Six of Crows ARC/Proof, The Gathering Dark, Nikolai Plush etc. It’s literally a shelf of collectibles because…that’s what I collect. It’s easier to say the whole shelf than one item on there, and it’s not like I could choose. That collection is always growing and I’m sure I’ll have new additions very soon.

So, there you have it. Top 5(ish) collectibles on my bookshelf. I’ve got to say, it was refreshing to talk about a topic that isn’t books, but still related to it.

Please let me know what memorabilia or significant collectibles you have on your bookshelf. I really want to know and the story behind them. Let me know in the Disqus comments! 

Thank you so much for reading and as always, likes, reblogs and comments are appreciated!
